instructions: Whisk eggs and milk together. Melt butter in a pan over medium heat. Pour in egg mixture and gently stir until cooked to desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook rice and let it cool. Dice chicken and cook in oil. Add beaten eggs and scramble. Add cooked rice, soy sauce, diced carrots, onions, and garlic. Stir-fry until combined.
Cook pasta. Fry bacon until crispy. Mix eggs and parmesan. Toss hot pasta with bacon, then remove from heat and quickly mix in egg mixture. Add garlic. Serve immediately.
Cook pasta. Sauté garlic and onion. Add diced tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes. Toss with pasta and top with parmesan cheese.
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces. Stir-fry in hot oil. Add sliced peppers, onions, and garlic. Add soy sauce. Serve over cooked rice.
Cook pasta. Brown ground beef. Sauté mushrooms, garlic, and onions. Add heavy cream and simmer. Combine with pasta.
Season and cook chicken breasts. Set aside. Sauté mushrooms, garlic, and onion. Add heavy cream and simmer. Pour over chicken.
Slice potatoes and fry until golden. Add onions and peppers. Pour beaten eggs over vegetables and cook until set.
Cook pasta. Melt butter and sauté minced garlic. Toss pasta with garlic butter. Top with grated parmesan.
Bread chicken with flour and egg. Fry until golden. Top with tomato sauce and mozzarella. Bake until cheese melts. Sprinkle with parmesan.
Cook rice. Scramble eggs and set aside. Stir-fry carrots, broccoli, garlic, and onion. Add rice, eggs, and soy sauce. Mix well.
Slice beef thinly. Stir-fry beef until browned. Add broccoli, garlic, and onion. Add soy sauce and cook until vegetables are tender. Serve over rice.
Cook pasta. Sauté garlic. Add spinach until wilted. Pour in heavy cream and simmer. Toss with pasta and parmesan.
Fry bacon until crispy. Remove and set aside. Fry eggs in bacon fat or butter. Serve together with toast.
Season chicken with salt and pepper. Sear in butter. Add minced garlic and lemon juice. Cook until chicken is done.
Dice potatoes and onions. Fry in butter until golden and crispy. Make wells and crack eggs into them. Cook until eggs are set.
Brown ground beef with onion and garlic. Add diced tomatoes and peppers. Season with spices. Serve in taco shells.
Sauté onion and garlic. Add rice and toast. Gradually add broth while stirring. Add sautéed mushrooms. Finish with parmesan.
Brown chicken pieces. Layer with uncooked rice, carrots, onions, and garlic in a baking dish. Add broth and butter. Bake covered.
Cook pasta and broccoli together. Drain. Sauté garlic in butter. Add heavy cream and mozzarella. Toss with pasta and broccoli.
Mix flour, eggs, and milk to make batter. Fold in diced apples. Cook pancakes in butter until golden on both sides.
Blend frozen banana with milk until smooth. Pour into bowl. Top with sliced apples and granola.
Sauté spinach and onion in butter. Beat eggs and pour over vegetables. Add crumbled feta. Fold omelet when set.
Cook pasta. Sauté diced chicken. Add garlic, onion, and diced tomatoes. Simmer. Toss with pasta. Top with parmesan.
Bake potatoes until tender. Cut open and fluff insides. Top with butter, heavy cream, crumbled bacon, and melted mozzarella.
